{
  "texts": [
    "JHEP04(2024)048Other than the vacuum representation, this provides the only highest weight representation of the k = 1 string.",
    "Focusing on the top representation, its highest weight states |m 1, m 2 ⟩ come from the R-sector of the theory and are labelled by quantum numbers m 1, m 2 given byJ 3 0 |m 1, m 2 ⟩ = (m 1 + m 2)|m 1, m 2 ⟩, U 0 |m 1, m 2 ⟩ = (m 1 -m 2 -1/2)|m 1, m 2 ⟩.The spin is defined by j = m 1 -m 2, so m 1 -m 2 = 1 2 will form a physical state condition.",
    "21In terms of the free fields, such states satisfyξ ± r |m 1, m 2 ⟩ = η ± r |m 1, m 2 ⟩ = 0,for all r ≥ 1, whilst the action of the zero modes is given byξ + 0 |m 1, m 2 ⟩ = |m 1, m 2 + 1/2⟩, η + 0 |m 1, m 2 ⟩ = 2m 1 |m 1 + 1/2, m 2 ⟩, ξ - 0 |m 1, m 2 ⟩ = -|m 1 -1/2, m 2 ⟩, η - 0 |m 1, m 2 ⟩ = -2m 2 |m 1, m 2 -1/2⟩.Likewise, for the fermionic modes, we have thatF + r |m 1, m 2 ⟩ = 0 for all r ≥ 0, F - r |m 1, m 2 ⟩ = 0 for all r ≥ 1,where F is either ψ or χ.",
    "This means that ψ - 0 and χ - 0 are creation modes.",
    "The physical spectrum also includes the spectrally flowed representations of (3.1)."
  ]
}